AIDS: Facts about the global spread of HIV and AIDS are presented in a list. An 
estimated 30 million people are HIV-infected and 12 million have died from AIDS. 
The epidemic currently has the highest concentrations in Africa, and India is 
expected to surpass this concentration within a few years. While HIV rates are 
decreasing in Thailand and Western Europe, they are increasing in the former 
Soviet Union. In the United States, AIDS deaths are decreasing, but the number 
of people living with HIV is not.

