The mortality of psychoanalysts.

Jeffery EH.

Comment in
    J Am Psychoanal Assoc. 2001 Winter;49(1):97-102.

The mortality rate for male psychoanalysts was compared to that for the general 
white male population; for male physicians; and for male psychiatrists and 
neurologists. For psychoanalysts the rate was found to be significantly lower 
than for any of the other three groups. Several possible explanations for this 
low mortality rate are considered. Two major factors may be the careful 
screening of candidates for psychoanalytic training and their personal analysis. 
Possible methods of controlling for these factors are suggested.

